# fr/tarot.ftl — French (français) translation
#
# Status: DRAFT — MEDIUM CONFIDENCE. Tarot terminology varies by tradition
# (Marseille vs. Rider-Waite-Smith). Cardpack's en-US uses Rider-Waite suits
# (Wands/Chalices/Swords/Pentacles), so this translation prefers the most
# widely-recognized French names. For Major Arcana that means Marseille-derived
# forms (Le Mat, Le Bateleur, La Papesse, etc.). A reviewer who prefers strict
# RWS-French (Le Fou, Le Magicien, La Grande Prêtresse) should adjust.
#
# Schema note: this file follows the en-US `name-rank-tarot-special-` prefix
# for Major Arcana. The de/tarot.ftl file uses bare `name-rank-tarot-` (no
# `-special-`) and is therefore broken — its Major Arcana names never resolve.

